</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h4 id="Non-CV-datasets">Non-CV datasets<a class="anchor-link" href="#Non-CV-datasets">&#182;</a></h4>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Note that we only considered CV datasets until now. I come from the CV field, but I do not pretend to focus in CV in this episode. However, these datasetys are actually the ones mostly used when testing the main Meta-Learning approaches. Alternatively, some regression tasks are also tested like in <a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/1703.03400.pdf">MAML</a>.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Experiment-definition">Experiment definition<a class="anchor-link" href="#Experiment-definition">&#182;</a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>There are two main components we may want to implement in the notebook: the challenge and the solution.</p>
<p>We will work in the Omniglot dataset since it is the most standard benchmark as well as it provides a hierarchy we will use to build the domain.</p>
<p>The challenge I propose to solve is <em>Learning to be able to solve, given a random alphabet, a character (within the alphabet) binary classification task with few samples</em>. Thus, our setting will go as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Build all the possible problems of this type in Omniglot:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Pick each combinations of 2 characters within all alphabets</p>
</li>
<li><p>For each combination, get all the samples and make common ML splits: train, validation and test</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Make splits of alphabets at Meta-Learning level: Meta-train, Meta-validation and Meta-test:</p>
<ul>
<li>For each Meta-split (Meta-sets from now on) take all possible problems for all its alphabets</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>We aim to be able to take any of the Meta-test problems and after a proper training of that problem, be able to solve its test set.</p>
<p>We rely in the fact that the Meta-sets will be enough varied (they will be randomly sorted) to represent the whole domain each.</p>
<p>As for the solution, we will use the MAML approach. Remember that this approach works by, at each meta-step, take a meta-batch of problems and for each problem compute an individual training (over its training samples) and evaluate the loss in its test set, averaging it over all the problems in the meta-batch and thus resulting in the meta-step loss.</p>
<p>I found in Github <a href="https://github.com/cbfinn/maml">the official implementation</a> of MAML by Chelsea Finn, in Tensorflow, as well as other unofficial implementations in Pytorch, like <a href="https://github.com/dragen1860/MAML-Pytorch">this one</a>. However, we want to take control of the implementations to bring it to our own experiment, so we will develop it from scratch (but following the ideas there).</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h3 id="Building-the-Meta-Splits">Building the Meta-Splits<a class="anchor-link" href="#Building-the-Meta-Splits">&#182;</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Ok, at this point we want to build each Meta-Split (or Meta-set). The material needs of a Meta-set are the alphabets it will contain. Remember that each Meta-set will determine its problems, but that is interpretable from its alphabets, since the problems will be all the possible problems of binary classification between characters of a same aphabet within the Meta-set.</p>
<p>We want to balance the Meta-set at character level, in a way in which each Meta-set will contain an approximation to a fixed ratio of characters, but respecting the constraint in which each whole alphabet must belong to a single Meta-set.</p>
<p>The simples way to do so is to take each empty Meta-set and add alphabets until the fixed ratio is reached, then the last Meta-set will get the remaining alphabets. This last Meta-set will be Meta-test, since lossing a bit of its content doesn't seem a disaster aside of its statistical significance.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>So first we will define a <em>MetaSplit</em> class that will contain this information. It will also contain some informative attributes such as the minimum number of characters, which will be computed at initialization depending on the Meta-set ratio and the total number of characters (these variables will be passed), the current number of characters (which will be updated out from the class when alphabets are added) and the number of problems, which will also be added from out of the class.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[20]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">class</span> <span class="nc">MetaSplit</span><span class="p">:</span>
  <span class="k">def</span> <span class="fm">__init__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ratio</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">total_num_characters</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">alphabets</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_characters</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
    <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">min_num_characters</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">total_num_characters</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">ratio</span>
    <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_problems</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">None</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>And let's initialize the Meta-splits (after this step they will still be empty)</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[21]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">metasplits</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span><span class="s1">&#39;metatrain&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">MetaSplit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">0.7</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_characters</span><span class="p">),</span>

<p>And finally let's shuffle the alphabets and split among the Meta-sets!</p>

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">

<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">

</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>As said, we will take each alphabet and add it to its corresponding Meta-set. To do so, we will begin with a given Meta-set (in our case the order is Meta-train, Meta-validation and Meta-test) and check if its internal number of characters has reached its minimum value so in case it does we will switch to the next Meta-set. In any case we will add the current alphabet to the current Meta-set and update the number of characters.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[22]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">current_metasplit</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;metatrain&#39;</span>
<span class="n">switch_metasplit_from</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span><span class="s1">&#39;metatrain&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s1">&#39;metaval&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;metaval&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s1">&#39;metatest&#39;</span><span class="p">}</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">alphabet</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">alphabets</span><span class="p">:</span>
  <span class="k">if</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="n">metasplits</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">current_metasplit</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_characters</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">metasplits</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">current_metasplit</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">min_num_characters</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">current_metasplit</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">switch_metasplit_from</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">current_metasplit</span><span class="p">]</span>
  <span class="n">metasplits</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">current_metasplit</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">alphabets</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">alphabet</span><span class="p">)</span>
  <span class="n">metasplits</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">current_metasplit</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_characters</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">chars_per_alphabet</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphabet</span><span class="p">]</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>We still have to compute the number of problems of each Meta-set, which depennds on its alphabets (and the number of characters in each of these alphabets).</p>
<p>I developed a formula to compute this which goes as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>As each problem's characters must be of the same alphabet, we can not group all characters in a single pool. Instead, we will compute it alphabet-wise and sum for all its alpabets. If we call $P$ the number of problems, $ P = \sum_{\alpha \in MS}{P_{\alpha}}$, where $P_{\alpha}$ is the number of problems in the alphabet $\alpha$ and $MS$ is the Meta-set (so the number of problems is the sum of the number of problems in each alphabet). This information is available right now (in the <em>MetaSplit</em> objects and the <em>chars_per_alphabet</em> variable).</p>
</li>
<li><p>The number of problems in an alphabet is the number of possible combinations of two characters among all belonging to the alphabet. From statistical theory, that is a Combination without repetition with combinations of 2, i.e. if $C_{\alpha}$ is the number of characters in the alphabet $\alpha$, ${C_{\alpha} \choose 2}$. We also know that ${m \choose n}$ is computed as $\frac{m!}{n! (m - n)!}$, so in our case ${C_{\alpha} \choose 2} = \frac{C_{\alpha}!}{2! (C_{\alpha} - 2)!}$.</p>
</li>
<li><p>We know that $2! = 2$. We also know that $\frac{C_{\alpha}!}{(C_{\alpha} - 2)!} = \frac{\prod_{1}^{C_{\alpha}}{i}}{\prod_{1}^{C_{\alpha} - 2}{j}} = \frac{\prod_{1}^{C_{\alpha} - 2}{i} \prod_{C_{\alpha} - 1}^{C_{\alpha}}{i}}{\prod_{1}^{C_{\alpha} - 2}{j}} = \frac{\prod_{1}^{C_{\alpha} - 2}{i}}{\prod_{1}^{C_{\alpha} - 2}{j}} \prod_{C_{\alpha} - 1}^{C_{\alpha}}{i} = 1 * \prod_{C_{\alpha} - 1}^{C_{\alpha}}{i} = (C_{\alpha}) * (C_{\alpha} - 1) = C_{\alpha}^2 - C_{\alpha}$.</p>
</li>
<li><p>So $P_{\alpha} = {C_{\alpha} \choose 2} = \frac{C_{\alpha}!}{2! (C_{\alpha} - 2)!} = \frac{1}{2!} * \frac{C_{\alpha}!}{(C_{\alpha} - 2)!} = \frac{1}{2} * (C_{\alpha}^2 - C_{\alpha}) = \frac{C_{\alpha}^2 - C_{\alpha}}{2}$.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Thus, $P = \sum_{\alpha \in MS}{P_{\alpha}} = \sum_{\alpha \in MS}{\frac{C_{\alpha}^2 - C_{\alpha}}{2}} = \frac{1}{2} \sum_{\alpha \in MS}{C_{\alpha}^2 - C_{\alpha}}$.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>So finally:</p>
<p>$P = \frac{\sum_{\alpha \in MS}{C_{\alpha}^2 - C_{\alpha}}}{2}$</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[23]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">metasplit</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">metasplits</span><span class="p">:</span>
  <span class="n">metasplits</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">metasplit</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_problems</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">chars_per_alphabet</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alph</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">chars_per_alphabet</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alph</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">alph</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">metasplits</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">metasplit</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">alphabets</span><span class="p">])</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Also recall that problems act as samples at the Meta-level, so we may count the number of metabatches with thios information if we know the metabatch size.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">

<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">metabatch_size</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">8</span>
<span class="n">num_metabatches</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">metasplits</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;metatrain&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_problems</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">metabatch_size</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>

</div>

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">

</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[25]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">num_metabatches</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="jp-RenderedText jp-OutputArea-output jp-OutputArea-executeResult" data-mime-type="text/plain">
<pre>1495</pre>
</div>

</div>

</div>

</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h3 id="The-Meta-level-DataLoader">The Meta-level DataLoader<a class="anchor-link" href="#The-Meta-level-DataLoader">&#182;</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>As we need to define DataLoaders when training a problem, which will generate the batches (samples + labels at each batch), at the Meta-level we will need an object that generates the meta-batches (problems at each meta-batch). We will call this the <em>MetaLoader</em>.</p>
<p>This Meta-Loader should give the tools to generate a DataLoader for each of its problems.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>So at this point let's explore the needs to create a problem DataLoader in our context. First, we need to define which will be the alphabet we will be working on. For simplicity, we will use the Latin alphabet as toy example. We will take all the characters of this alphabet from the list.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[26]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">toy_alphabet</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Latin&#39;</span>
<span class="n">toy_characters</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">char</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">char</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">characters</span> <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">char</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;/&#39;</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">toy_alphabet</span><span class="p">]</span>
</pre></div>

<p>We picked both the 10th and the 11th characters from the latin alphabets. These are <em>J</em> and <em>K</em> (count it if you wish to). Let's continue to see if this matches.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">

<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Now we want to get which samples in the dataset correspond to this character. Recall that in torchvision's Omniglot, samples are sequential with 20 samples per character, so we aim to get the position of the characters in the list of characters and therefore the position of its samples in the dataset. This last value corresponds to the range of values between the character position (in the whole list) multiplied by 20 and the character position +1 multiplied by 20 (the beginning of the following character range). We want a flattened list of these sample indices for both characters in the problem.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[32]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">toy_problem_char_idx</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">characters</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">tchar</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">tchar</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">toy_problem_characters</span><span class="p">]</span>  <span class="c1">#  position of the characters in the list of characters</span>
<span class="n">toy_problem_samples_idx</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">toy_sample_range</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">tcharidx</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">toy_problem_char_idx</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">toy_sample_range</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">tcharidx</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">tcharidx</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)]</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">

     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">toy_problem_samples_idx</span>
</pre></div>

<p>This length makes sense since we have 2 characters with 20 samples each.</p>

<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">

<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Now we need to explicitly tell the dataloader to take among these samples. The problem is that the Omniglot dataset from torchvision cannot be split as far as we know. Instead, we may make use of the torch's <a href="https://pytorch.org/docs/stable/data.html#torch.utils.data.SubsetRandomSampler">SubsetRandomSampler object</a>, which explicitly tells which samples to randomly take. Furthermore, we want these samples to be taken by batches, so we will also wrap it into a <a href="https://pytorch.org/docs/stable/data.html#torch.utils.data.BatchSampler">BatchSampler</a>.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>

<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">indexer</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">BatchSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">SubsetRandomSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">toy_problem_samples_idx</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">batch_size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">8</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">drop_last</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>So now we may directly create a DataLoader with the raw Omniglot dataset using this sampler object that will directly serve us random batches of samples of the characters of our problems, as we want. We will use <em>shuffle=False</em> since the sampler already shuffles the samples.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[37]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">problem_loader</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DataLoader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dataset</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">omniglot_raw</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">shuffle</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">batch_sampler</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">indexer</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Now let's review both samples and labels from the Data Loader. We want to verify that samples are what we expect (shape of <em>batch_size x num_channels x width x height</em>, i.e. 8 x 1 x 105 x 105), that images correspond to <em>J</em>'s and <em>K</em>'s and that labels are randomly shuffled.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">

<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">

  <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;batch &#39;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ibatch</span><span class="p">))</span>
  <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">batch</span><span class="p">))</span>

  <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">batch</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>
</pre></div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">figure</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">))</span>

  <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">isample</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">sample</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">batch</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]):</span>

<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>So as we see, everythin matches our needs.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Now that we defined a DataLoader for the problem, we are ready to create the Meta-Loaders.</p>
<p>A Meta-Loader object should, at each step, be able to return a batch of problem DataLoaders. As we saw before, these DataLoaders should return at least the indices of the samples to use at each batch, and then at training/validation/test time the indices will point to the data to load from the Omniglot raw dataset. We could also work with DataLoaders that directly deliver the data, but since we would be creating lots of dataloaders with raw data, the memory cost could be too high. That is the main reason why we will work with indices instead.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>So, what should the MetaLoader class contain? Making it simple, we will just need its initialization and an <strong>iter</strong> method that will be returning us the problem loaders at each meta-batch. The rest should be internal methods. And how should this mandatory methods work?</p>
<p>Well, when initializing a MetaLoader it will load the necessary info at both Meta-level and Learning level, as well as it will initialize a sampler as we saw before at the DataLoader but now for the Meta-Level, which will be run at <em>__iter__</em>. This sampler will just sample from the problem indices (so one of the variables at the Meta-level must be the number of problems in the meta-set, that can be computed as explained before) for the same reason as before, memory optimization.</p>
<p>Then at <em>__iter__</em> time the sampler will return a batch of problem indices. From each of these indices we will make a method (<em>__get_problem_loader__</em> method) to get the corresponding problem loader, which will begin searching the alphabet and the characters in the alphabet for each problem index and then the samples index in this problem(<em>__problem_idx_to_samples_idx__</em> method), for further problem loader building (<em>__build_problem_loader_from_samples__</em> method, which will return the three loaders of the problem for train, validation and test).</p>
<p>Thus, when iterating the MetaLoader object, we will at each meta-batch receive a list of (meta-batch size) dictionaries with keys train, validation and test where for each key the corresponding set DataLoader of the problem will be contained.</p>

<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">class</span> <span class="nc">MetaLoader</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="sd">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="sd">    &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="fm">__init__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">base_dataset</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">metabatch_size</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">batch_sizes</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                 <span class="n">chars_per_alphabet</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">problem_ratios</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">base_dataset</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">base_dataset</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">metabatch_size</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">metabatch_size</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">batch_sizes</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">batch_sizes</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">chars_per_alph</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">chars_per_alphabet</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">problem_ratios</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.15</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.1</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">problems_per_alph</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_problems</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">__load_quantitative_info__</span><span class="p">()</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">metasampler</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">BatchSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">RandomSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_problems</span><span class="p">)),</span> 
                                        <span class="n">batch_size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">metabatch_size</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                                        <span class="n">drop_last</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">__load_quantitative_info__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">alphb</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">chars_per_alph</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">problems_per_alph</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">chars_per_alph</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">-</span> 
                                                <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">chars_per_alph</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
            <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_problems</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">problems_per_alph</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">]</span>
    
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">__has_reached__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">idx</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ctr</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">current</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">ctr</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">current</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="n">idx</span>
    
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">__problem_idx_to_samples_idx__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">problem_idx</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                                       <span class="n">prbs_on_prev_alphabets</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                                       <span class="n">chars_on_prev_alphabets</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">pb_idx_in_alph</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">problem_idx</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">prbs_on_prev_alphabets</span>
        <span class="n">ichars_in_alphabet</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pb_idx_in_alph</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">chars_per_alph</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">]),</span> 
                                <span class="n">pb_idx_in_alph</span> <span class="o">%</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">chars_per_alph</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">])</span>
        <span class="n">ichars</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">tuple</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">ich</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">chars_on_prev_alphabets</span> \
                        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">ich</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">ichars_in_alphabet</span><span class="p">])</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">sample_idx</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">charidx</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">ichars</span> 
                <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">sample_idx</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">charidx</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">charidx</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)]</span>
    
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">__build_problem_loader_from_samples__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">samples_idx</span><span class="p">):</span>

        <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">shuffle</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">samples_idx</span><span class="p">)</span>

        <span class="n">train_val_frontier</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">samples_idx</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">problem_ratios</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span>
        <span class="n">val_test_frontier</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">train_val_frontier</span> <span class="o">+</span> 
                                <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">samples_idx</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">problem_ratios</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>
        
        <span class="n">samples_idx_train</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">samples_idx</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="n">train_val_frontier</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="n">samples_idx_val</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">samples_idx</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">train_val_frontier</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">val_test_frontier</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="n">samples_idx_test</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">samples_idx</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">val_test_frontier</span><span class="p">:]</span>

        <span class="n">train_sampler</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">BatchSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">SubsetRandomSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">samples_idx_train</span><span class="p">),</span> 
                                     <span class="n">batch_size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">batch_sizes</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;train&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> 
                                     <span class="n">drop_last</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">val_sampler</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">BatchSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">SubsetRandomSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">samples_idx_val</span><span class="p">),</span> 
                                   <span class="n">batch_size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">batch_sizes</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;val&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> 
                                   <span class="n">drop_last</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">test_sampler</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">BatchSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">SubsetRandomSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">samples_idx_test</span><span class="p">),</span> 
                                    <span class="n">batch_size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">batch_sizes</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;test&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> 
                                    <span class="n">drop_last</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">loaders</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span><span class="s1">&#39;train&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">DataLoader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dataset</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">base_dataset</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                                       <span class="n">batch_sampler</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">train_sampler</span><span class="p">),</span>
                   <span class="s1">&#39;val&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">DataLoader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dataset</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">base_dataset</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                                       <span class="n">batch_sampler</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">val_sampler</span><span class="p">),</span>
                   <span class="s1">&#39;test&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">DataLoader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dataset</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">base_dataset</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                                       <span class="n">batch_sampler</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">test_sampler</span><span class="p">)}</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">loaders</span>

        
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">__get_problem_loader__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">problem_idx</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">pbs_ctr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
        <span class="n">chars_ctr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">alphb</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">chars_per_alph</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">__has_reached__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">problem_idx</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pbs_ctr</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                                        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">problems_per_alph</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">]):</span>
                <span class="n">pbs_ctr</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">problems_per_alph</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">]</span>
                <span class="n">chars_ctr</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">chars_per_alph</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">]</span>
            <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">problem_samples_idx</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">__problem_idx_to_samples_idx__</span><span class="p">(</span>
                    <span class="n">problem_idx</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alphb</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pbs_ctr</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">chars_ctr</span><span class="p">)</span>
                <span class="k">return</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">__build_problem_loader_from_samples__</span><span class="p">(</span>
                    <span class="n">problem_samples_idx</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">def</span>  <span class="fm">__iter__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">imetabatch</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">metabatch</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">metasampler</span><span class="p">):</span>
            <span class="n">problem_loaders</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
            <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">problem_idx</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">metabatch</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">problem_loaders</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">__get_problem_loader__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">problem_idx</span><span class="p">))</span>
            <span class="k">yield</span> <span class="n">problem_loaders</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">class</span> <span class="nc">SimpleNet</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Module</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="fm">__init__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="nb">super</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="fm">__init__</span><span class="p">()</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">conv1</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Conv2d</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">6</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">conv2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Conv2d</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">6</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">conv3</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Conv2d</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">12</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">conv4</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Conv2d</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">12</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">16</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pool</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">MaxPool2d</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fc1</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Linear</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">16</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fc2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Linear</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">forward</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pool</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">F</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">relu</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">conv1</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)))</span>
        <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pool</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">F</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">relu</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">conv2</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)))</span>
        <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pool</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">F</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">relu</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">conv3</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)))</span>
        <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pool</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">F</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">relu</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">conv4</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)))</span>
        <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">torch</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">flatten</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">F</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">relu</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fc1</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">))</span>
        <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">F</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sigmoid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fc2</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">))</span>
        <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">squeeze</span><span class="p">()</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">x</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">

<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Now we will define also our Loss function as well as our optimizer (we will use SGD for simpllicity). We will train 15 epochs in the problem and run a validation step at the end of an epoch.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[51]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">model</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">SimpleNet</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">criterion</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">BCEWithLogitsLoss</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">optimizer</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">optim</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">SGD</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">parameters</span><span class="p">(),</span> <span class="n">lr</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.01</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">momentum</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.9</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[52]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">n_epochs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">15</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>We will need the following methods to process both labels and samples (for the labels we just one to convert both labels in 0 and 1 respectively).</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[53]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">process_labels</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels_raw</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span><span class="p">):</span>
  <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels_raw</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">float</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">preprocess_inputs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">inputs</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">255</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">

<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>So we are ready to implement and run what we defined.</p>

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">

</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[54]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">ref_label</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">None</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">n_epochs</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Epoch </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">running_loss</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>
    <span class="n">val_loss</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>
    <span class="n">val_accuracy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">data</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">toy_problem_loader</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">inputs_raw</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels_raw</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span>
        <span class="n">optimizer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">zero_grad</span><span class="p">()</span>
        <span class="n">inputs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">preprocess_inputs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs_raw</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">outputs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">ref_label</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">labels_raw</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="n">labels</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">process_labels</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels_raw</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">loss</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">criterion</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">outputs</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">loss</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">backward</span><span class="p">()</span>
        <span class="n">optimizer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">step</span><span class="p">()</span>
        <span class="n">running_loss</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">()</span>
        <span class="n">accuracy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(((</span><span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">outputs</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">outputs</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">float</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">labels</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">outputs</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">shape</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Epoch </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">, step </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">:</span><span class="s1">5d</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">], Loss: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">, Accuracy: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">accuracy</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">iv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">datav</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">toy_problem_loader_val</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">inputs_rawv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels_rawv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datav</span>
        <span class="n">inputsv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">preprocess_inputs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs_rawv</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">outputsv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputsv</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">labelsv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">process_labels</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels_rawv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">lossv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">criterion</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">outputsv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelsv</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span>
        <span class="n">val_loss</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">lossv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">()</span>
        <span class="n">val_accuracy</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="p">(((</span><span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">outputsv</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">outputsv</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">float</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">labelsv</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Epoch </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">, VALIDATION], Loss: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">val_loss</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">iv</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">, Accuracy: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">val_accuracy</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">iv</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Finished Training&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">

<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h3 id="Train-with-manual-GD-algorithm">Train with manual GD algorithm<a class="anchor-link" href="#Train-with-manual-GD-algorithm">&#182;</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Before concluding I am a maniac by trying this for no reason, let's take a look at <a href="https://github.com/cbfinn/maml">MAML official implementation on Github</a>. In the <a href="https://github.com/cbfinn/maml/blob/master/maml.py#L79"><em>maml.py</em></a> module you can realize that at Learning level, authors also update manually the weights at each step. The same goes for <a href="https://github.com/dragen1860/MAML-Pytorch">unofficial Pytorch implementations</a>. Why is this? Well, if you think, in Meta-Learning, the model must learn at 2 levels. I.e. gradients, losses, optimizers, etc must work at 2 levels at the same time, which ML frameworks are not made for. Updating the weights manually in one of both levels is actually a workaround to this issue, so from Pytorch perspective there is no Learning level, and it just knows the updates at Meta-Learning level.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">

</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>So, before going for the Meta-Learning level we will manually train the same as before but now with manual updates. Note that updating model's parameters is done though the code chunk:</p>

<pre><code>for param, param_key in zip(new_weights, param_keys):
            model._modules[param_key[0]]._parameters[param_key[1]] = param</code></pre>

</div>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">n_epochs</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Epoch </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

        <span class="n">inputs_raw</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels_raw</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span>

        <span class="n">new_weights</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">map</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">p</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">p</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">update_lr</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">p</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="nb">zip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grads</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">new_weights</span><span class="p">)))</span>

<h3 id="Meta-Learning-training">Meta-Learning training<a class="anchor-link" href="#Meta-Learning-training">&#182;</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>At this point we will directly define the Meta-Learning pipeline as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li>At each Meta-epoch, the Meta-train MetaLoader is called at each Meta-train meta-step.</li>
<li>At each Meta-train meta-step, a each problem is the meta-batch is asked for its DataLoaders</li>
<li>For the train DataLoader, at each epoch each step is called and the batch is predicted.</li>
<li>Manually, at this step the model weights are updated</li>
<li>In the end of the epoch, a validation is run</li>
<li>In the last epoch, the validation loss is computed normally but the model is returned to its original (at the beginning of the problem) state.</li>
<li>The same is repeated over all the problems in the meta-batch and all final validation losses are averaged.</li>
<li>A pyorch update is performed in the end of the meta-batch</li>
<li>Every 1000 meta-steps a Meta-Validation meta-step is performed. The process is the same as in Meta-train but the loss won't update the model (only computed for Meta-training guidance matters).</li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[56]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">make_step</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">outputs</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">update_lr</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">in_weights</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">loss</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">criterion</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">outputs</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">grads</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">torch</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">autograd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grad</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">parameters</span><span class="p">())</span>
    <span class="n">out_weights</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">map</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">p</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">p</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">update_lr</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">p</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="nb">zip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grads</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">in_weights</span><span class="p">)))</span>
    <span class="n">accuracy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(((</span><span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">outputs</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">outputs</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">float</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">labels</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">outputs</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">shape</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">out_weights</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">accuracy</span>
</pre></div>

</pre></div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">model</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">SimpleNet</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">criterion</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">BCEWithLogitsLoss</span><span class="p">()</span>
