<span class="n">param_keys</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">mod</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">kname</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">mod</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">_modules</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">kname</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">_modules</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">mod</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">_parameters</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">metaepoch</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">n_metaepochs</span><span class="p">):</span>

    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;===============================&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;//           Meta-Epoch </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">metaepoch</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">       //&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>    
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;===============================&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">mi</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">metabatch</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">metatrain_loader</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1">#  Meta-step</span>
        <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">mi</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1"> updates at Meta-Level&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

        <span class="n">running_loss</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>  <span class="c1">#  At each meta-step, the loss is reset</span>

        <span class="n">initial_weights</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">parameters</span><span class="p">()</span>

        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">problem_loaders</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">metabatch</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1">#  Problem in the meta-batch</span>

            <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;- Problem </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">pi</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1"> -&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="n">problem_loader</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">problem_loaders</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;train&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
            <span class="n">problem_loader_val</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">problem_loaders</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;val&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
            <span class="n">ref_label</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">None</span>

            <span class="n">new_weights</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">initial_weights</span>

            <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">n_epochs</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1">#  Epoch in the problem training</span>

                <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Epoch </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

                <span class="n">val_loss</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>
                <span class="n">val_accuracy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>

                <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">data</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">problem_loader</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1">#  Step in the problem</span>

                    <span class="n">inputs_raw</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels_raw</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span>
                    <span class="n">inputs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">preprocess_inputs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs_raw</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="n">outputs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        <span class="n">ref_label</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">labels_raw</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>   <span class="c1">#  On a new problem (1st step) adjust label mapping</span>
                    <span class="n">labels</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">process_labels</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels_raw</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="n">new_weights</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">accuracy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">make_step</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">outputs</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">update_lr</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">new_weights</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="n">update_model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">new_weights</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">param_keys</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#  At each step in the problem manually update the model</span>

                    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Epoch </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">, step </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">:</span><span class="s1">5d</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">], Loss: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">, Accuracy: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">accuracy</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

                <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">iv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">datav</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">problem_loader_val</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1">#  At the end of the training process in an epoch of a problem we compute a whole validation</span>

                    <span class="n">inputs_rawv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels_rawv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datav</span>
                    <span class="n">inputsv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">preprocess_inputs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs_rawv</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="n">outputsv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputsv</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="n">labelsv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">process_labels</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels_rawv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="n">lossv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">criterion</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">outputsv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelsv</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span>  <span class="c1">#  Loss in a validation batch</span>
                    <span class="n">val_loss</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">lossv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">()</span>
                    <span class="n">val_accuracy</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="p">(((</span><span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">outputsv</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">outputsv</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">float</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">labelsv</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>

                <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Epoch </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">, VALIDATION], Loss: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">val_loss</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">iv</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">, Accuracy: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">val_accuracy</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">iv</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#  Loss and accuracy averaged for all validation batches in the problem, displayed after whole validation</span>

            <span class="n">running_loss</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">lossv</span>  <span class="c1">#  After all epochs (all training process) in a single problem the validation loss is added</span>

            <span class="n">update_model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_weights</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">param_keys</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1"># After the whole train + validation of a problem and the final loss is added, return the model to its original stage in the meta-step </span>
        
        <span class="n">metastep_loss</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">running_loss</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">metabatch_size</span>  <span class="c1">#  The added validation losses of all problems in the metabatch are averaged</span>

        <span class="n">metaoptimizer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">zero_grad</span><span class="p">()</span>  <span class="c1">#  We perform gradient descent at the Meta-Level over the averaged validation loss</span>
        <span class="n">metastep_loss</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">backward</span><span class="p">()</span>
        <span class="n">metaoptimizer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">step</span><span class="p">()</span>

        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">mi</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">%</span> <span class="mi">1000</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">:</span>  <span class="c1">#  Meta-validation performed every 1000 meta-steps</span>

            <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;META-VALIDATION STEP:&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">mbvi</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">metabatch_val</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">metaval_loader</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1">#  Meta-validation meta-step</span>

                <span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">mbvi</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">%</span> <span class="mi">10</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">:</span>

                    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Validation step </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">mbvi</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    
                <span class="n">initial_weights</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">parameters</span><span class="p">()</span>

                <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">problem_loaders</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">metabatch_val</span><span class="p">:</span>  <span class="c1">#  Problem in the meta-validation meta-batch</span>

                    <span class="n">problem_loader</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">problem_loaders</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;train&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
                    <span class="n">problem_loader_val</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">problem_loaders</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;val&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
                    <span class="n">ref_label</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">None</span>
                    <span class="n">new_weights</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">initial_weights</span>

                    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">epoch</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">n_epochs</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1">#  Epoch in the problem training</span>

                        <span class="n">val_loss</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>
                        <span class="n">val_accuracy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>

                        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">data</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">problem_loader</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1">#  Step in the problem</span>
                            
                            <span class="n">inputs_raw</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels_raw</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span>
                            <span class="n">inputs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">preprocess_inputs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs_raw</span><span class="p">)</span>
                            <span class="n">outputs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs</span><span class="p">)</span>
                            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
                                <span class="n">ref_label</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">labels_raw</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
                            <span class="n">labels</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">process_labels</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels_raw</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span><span class="p">)</span>

                            <span class="n">new_weights</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">accuracy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">make_step</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">outputs</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">update_lr</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">new_weights</span><span class="p">)</span>
                            <span class="n">update_model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">new_weights</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">param_keys</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#  Note that we still need to update although being in (Meta-)validation. That is because we are in meta-validation but at the Learning level we are in training stage</span>

                        <span class="c1">#    print(f&#39;Epoch {epoch + 1}, step {i + 1:5d}], Loss: {loss.item()}, Accuracy: {accuracy}&#39;)</span>

                        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">iv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">datav</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">problem_loader_val</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1">#  At the end of the training process in an epoch of a problem we compute a whole validation, as in Meta-Train</span>

                            <span class="n">inputs_rawv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labels_rawv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datav</span>
                            <span class="n">inputsv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">preprocess_inputs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputs_rawv</span><span class="p">)</span>
                            <span class="n">outputsv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inputsv</span><span class="p">)</span>
                            <span class="n">labelsv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">process_labels</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels_rawv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ref_label</span><span class="p">)</span>
                            
                            <span class="n">lossv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">criterion</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">outputsv</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelsv</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span>
                            <span class="n">val_loss</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">lossv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">()</span>
                            <span class="n">val_accuracy</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="p">(((</span><span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">outputsv</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">outputsv</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">float</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">labelsv</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>

                    
                    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">mbvi</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">%</span> <span class="mi">10</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">:</span>

                        <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Last epoch, VALIDATION], Loss: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">val_loss</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">iv</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">, Accuracy: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">val_accuracy</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">iv</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1"># The Meta-Validation only runs for informative matters, so our goal is to have this at the end of each problem (every 10 steps)</span>

                    <span class="n">update_model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_weights</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">param_keys</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;END OF META-VALIDATION STEP&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
